21 June 2013 Acting Cabinet Spokesperson and GCIS CEO, Ms Phumla Williams and Media Development and Diversity Agency CEO, Mr Lumko Mtinde will on Friday, 21 June 2013 brief members of the media on the outcomes of the Community Media Forum held in Pretoria on Thursday, 20 June 2013 and Friday. The aim of the two day forum was to review the community media sector in South Africa and to establish how best the government can assist the sector to ensure transformation in the media industry. The details are as follows: Date: Friday, 21 June 2013 Time: 13h00 Venue: Tshedimosetso House, 1035 Francis Baard Street, Corner Festival Street, Hatfield, Pretoria NB: There will be a video link to Imbizo Media Centre, 120 Plein Street, Parliament, and Cape Town RSVP: Professor Ndawonde (Pretoria) E-mail: proffesor@gcis.gov.za Cell: 0735979534 Loedfie Hendrikse (Cape Town) E-mail: Loedfieh@gcis.gov.za Cell: 0826704145 Enquiries: Phumla Williams 0835010139 Issued by Government Communication and Information System (GCIS)